commentPreTextItems.html: scores are level. Afridi on strike. The bowler suddenly stops short and Afridi practices a forward defensive stroke

commentTextItems.html: down the leg side, Afridi decides to let it go and waits for the umpire's call. He can't seal it with a six. The crowd won't mind though because they've witnessed yet another victory at this ground. That's seven out of seven

commentPostTextItems.html: A comprehensive victory in the end, despite the blimp in the middle overs when Zimbabwe plugged the gaps and restricted the scoring. Zimbabwe will feel they were at least 40-50 runs short. Their lower order couldn't quite maintain the momentum set by Taibu and Masakadza and the game was lost after both were dismissed. However, their efforts in the field cannot be ignored and coach Robin Brown should feel proud that his side managed to give the home side a few anxious moments.

Pakistan may not make too many changes for the forthcoming games. Jamshed's had two impressive outings but the same can't be said for Samiullah Khan. Perhaps it's time to unleash a few tearaway quicks like Sohail Khan, says Faras Ghani, our man at the ground.
The Man of the Match is Sohail Tanvir for his 4 for 34.

That's it from us here. Do join us for the third one-dayer on the 27th of January in Multan. Remember it's a day-night game, starting at 11.00 local time (06.00 GMT). On behalf of my crew, this is Kanishkaa signing off. Cheers!

commentTextItems.html: slides towards the pads, Yousuf responds to the calls of the crowd by taking a single, he nudges to the on side
defended quietly on the front foot
half volley outside off, Afridi stays at the crease, gets his bat down and scoops through the line and deposits the ball over long-off

headshotImage.caption: Mohammad Yousuf player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Yousuf player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: on the blockhole outside the off stump, he digs it out to mid-off
good length on middle and leg, Afridi stays back and pulls with intent over midwicket, there was nobody there to cut it off
full toss on middle and leg, Afridi pulls but can't beat midwicket
cut away off the meat of the bat to deep extra cover
Dropped: but a brilliant effort by Sibanda, Afridi slices uppishly on the front foot, Sibanda runs to his left, nearly catches it one-handed, he appears to have it in control but the ball slips out
Chigumbura keeps him quiet again, Yousuf defends back to the bowler and gives Afridi the strike

headshotImage.caption: Mohammad Yousuf player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Yousuf player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: pushed to the off side, good over by Chigumbura so far
fuller in length outside the off stump, Yousuf digs it out to the Dabengwa at mid-off
good length on off stump, gets it to drift in, Yousuf shows the full face of the bat and defends
pitches outside off, gets on the back foot and punches to the covers

commentPreTextItems.html: Afridi wants this wrapped up fast

commentTextItems.html: pitches outside off, Afridi opens the face of the bat and glides it down to third man
driven on the front foot to extra cover

commentTextItems.html: cut away wide of point and the sweeper cover runs across to cut it off

Dropped: Masakadza the culprit.... Afridi goes for broke and mis-hits it, the ball is skied for an eternity and the bowler tries to get under it but loses sight as the ball slips through his fingers, the crowd aren't complaining
pushed behind point for a single
on the blockhole, dug out to the on side

dismissalText.long: c Shoaib Malik b Sohail Tanvir
dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor c Shoaib Malik b Sohail Tanvir 26 (35b 1x4 1x6 36m) SR: 74.28

dismissalComment.html: the slower ball again, pitches on a fullish length outside off, Taylor tries to loft over the off side but stays rooted to the crease, Malik runs backwards from extra cover and takes a well-judged catch

dismissalText.long: c Younis Khan b Shoaib Malik
dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Younis Khan b Shoaib Malik 1 (3b 0x4 0x6 4m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: Pakistan are pulling it back here.... gives it plenty of air outside the off stump, Chigumbura stays at the crease and tries to go downtown, he connects but fails to get the desired elevation, Younis runs to his left from deep midwicket and takes it low forward

dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu c †Kamran Akmal b Sohail Tanvir 81 (111b 3x4 0x6 144m) SR: 72.97

dismissalComment.html: Akmal gets the thin edge.... slower ball outside the off stump, Taibu gives room and tries to cut, the ball kicks up a little, gets a thin edge through to Akmal. Taibu knows it and he starts walking before umpire de Silva raises the finger

dismissalText.long: c sub (Fawad Alam) b Iftikhar Anjum
dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams c sub (Fawad Alam) b Iftikhar Anjum 3 (6b 0x4 0x6 9m) SR: 50

dismissalComment.html: the bowling change works..... deceives Williams with a slower one, he lofts from the crease and tries to clear long-on, he fails to get the distance and hits it down substitute Fawad Alam's throat

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri b Iftikhar Anjum 1 (3b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: Rao gets him with reverse swing... gets the ball to drift in from off and middle, Matsikenyeri tries to work it through the off side, gets beaten and the ball cannons onto the leg stump, sending it back a few yards

dismissalText.commentary: Salman Butt c †Taibu b Chigumbura 17 (28b 2x4 0x6 26m) SR: 60.71

dismissalComment.html: loose stroke, pitches on a good length on middle and shapes away, the ball bounces a bit more than expected and Butt lunges forward instead of staying back, he flashes at it and gets a thick edge through to Taibu

image.caption: Ray Price
image.longCaption: Ray Price portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Nasir Jamshed run out (Price) 74 (64b 14x4 0x6 90m) SR: 115.62

dismissalComment.html: excellent work by Price....Jamshed punches the ball on the back foot to the left Price, he sets off for a single which wasn't there, Price gathers the ball and in the same action flings it back at the stumps, Jamshed is about a couple of yards short of his crease and he dives in vain

image.caption: Ray Price
image.longCaption: Ray Price portrait, World Cup 2011, February 11, 2011

dismissalText.commentary: Younis Khan run out (Sibanda) 35 (31b 3x4 0x6 68m) SR: 112.9

dismissalComment.html: that's two for the over! Yousuf turns it towards Sibanda at midwicket with soft hands and sets off, Sibanda gathers the ball in a flash and flicks it low to the striker's end, a direct hit finds Younis short of the crease. He doesn't wait for the umpire, he just walks off

dismissalText.commentary: Shoaib Malik st †Taibu b Price 4 (16b 0x4 0x6 16m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: superb stuff from Taibu! Malik lunges forward to drive but the ball catches the toe of his bat, hits his pad and rolls close to the stumps. Taibu gathers the ball and breaks the stumps with Malik short of the crease. Zimbabwe know they've got him and the third umpire reconfirms that

dismissalText.commentary: Misbah-ul-Haq c Taylor b Masakadza 20 (50b 2x4 0x6 46m) SR: 40

dismissalComment.html: Misbah tries to launch this out of the ground but mis-hits it, he stays at the crease, gets on his knee and the ball is skied for a long time, Taylor at mid-on takes a few paces backwards and takes the catch, falling over to his right

dismissalText.commentary: Shahid Afridi not out 43 (27b 4x4 2x6 33m) SR: 159.25

stories.title: We spilled opportunities at crucial junctures - Masakadza
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v Zimbabwe, 2nd ODI, Hyderabad
stories.seoTitle: We spilled opportunities at crucial junctures - Masakadza
stories.summary:
Hamilton Masakadza rued the number of dropped chances, which he blamed for
his side's defeat against Pakistan

stories.title: Tanvir takes charge of Pakistan attack
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v Zimbabwe, 2nd ODI, Hyderabad
stories.seoTitle: Tanvir takes charge of Pakistan attack
stories.summary:
The novelty of Sohail Tanvir's action may be wearing off, but little about
his performances since his debut last year suggest the potency of his
bowling is going the same way

stories.title: Tanvir and Jamshed seal victory
stories.subTitle: Pakistan v Zimbabwe, 2nd ODI, Hyderabad
stories.summary:
Nasir Jamshed scored his second successive half-century and Shahid Afridi
notched an unbeaten 43 to guide Pakistan past Zimbabwe in the second ODI of the Mobilink Cup in Hyderabad. Pakistan lead the series 2-0 with three to play
